# Project status (as of 2026-07)

## Product

- Private algorithm note catalog: structured filters (Path 1) + retrieve → list → answer Ask (Path 2).
- Stack: Next.js + HeroUI v3 + Better Auth | FastAPI + SQLAlchemy/Alembic | Postgres 17 + pgvector.
- **MVP is live** at `https://algonote.keyneswu.com` (HTTPS reverse proxy + Cloudflare).
- Shipped & archived OpenSpec changes (no active change): init, i18n/dark UI, notes retrieval UX, notes list browse, note dedup/merge, ask multi-turn, settings password management.
- Auth: public signup off; first admin via `/setup`; admins manage users + password reset in Settings; self-service password change exists.

## Production deploy (current practice)

Prefer **manual SSH deploy** until GitHub Actions SSH auth is cleaned up. Do not assume Actions works.

```bash
ssh ubuntu@<SERVER_IP>
cd ~/dev/projects/AlgoNoteHelper
git pull
docker compose up --build -d
```

- Server `.env` stays on the host (not in git). Production URLs must be the HTTPS domain (`BETTER_AUTH_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`, `CORS_ORIGINS`) — not localhost.
- Named volume `pgdata` **persists** across `up --build`; never use `docker compose down -v` unless wiping data on purpose.
- `compose up --build` rebuilds `api`/`frontend` images; DB data and server `.env` are reused. Schema/auth migrations are **not** automatic — run Alembic / `pnpm dlx auth@latest migrate` only when needed.
- Keep real server IPs out of committed files (`.env.example` uses placeholders).

## GitHub Actions

- `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` exists (SSH → pull → compose) but CI deploy is **unreliable** (SSH key hygiene / secret mismatch). Treat as optional; do not block feature work on fixing it unless the user asks.

## Agent guidance

- Assume prod is running and has real user/admin data — avoid destructive DB/volume advice.
- New features: prefer OpenSpec propose/apply when the user wants structured changes.
- Deploy help: default to the manual SSH flow above; mention Actions only if asked.
